                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-09T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>374. Your telegram No. 810, November 5, 9 p.m. It is understood by the Department
                    that the reduction of the number of marines is to be gradual; that at the
                    present time it is proposed to withdraw from Tientsin 300 men; and that before
                    any further reduction is made the entire matter in regard to the place from
                    which additional men will be taken, will be reconsidered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
